Dame Enid Diana Elizabeth Rigg , DBE -LRB- born 20 July 1938 -RRB- is an English actress .
She is known for playing Emma Peel in the 1960s TV series The Avengers -LRB- 1965 -- 68 -RRB- , and Olenna Tyrell in Game of Thrones -LRB- 2013 -- present -RRB- .
She has also had an extensive career in theatre , including playing the title role in Medea , both in London and New York , for which she won the 1994 Tony Award for Best Actress in a Play .
She was made a CBE in 1988 and a Dame in 1994 .
Rigg made her professional stage debut in 1957 in The Caucasian Chalk Circle , and joined the Royal Shakespeare Company in 1959 .
She made her Broadway debut in the 1971 production of Abelard & Heloise .
Her film roles include Helena in A Midsummer Night 's Dream -LRB- 1968 -RRB- ; Countess Teresa di Vicenzo , wife of James Bond in On Her Majesty 's Secret Service -LRB- 1969 -RRB- ; Lady Holiday in The Great Muppet Caper -LRB- 1981 -RRB- ; and Arlene Marshall in Evil Under the Sun -LRB- 1982 -RRB- .
She won the BAFTA TV Award for Best Actress for the 1989 BBC miniseries Mother Love , and an Emmy Award for her role as Mrs. Danvers in the 1997 adaptation of Rebecca .
Her other television credits include You , Me and the Apocalypse -LRB- 2015 -RRB- , and opposite her daughter , Rachael Stirling , in Detectorists -LRB- 2015 -RRB- .